 <img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1453655" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/School-Curriculum.jpg?resize=640%2C361&#038;ssl=1" alt="Maitama Sule University Kano to resume lectures Jan 18 — Official" width="640" height="361" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/School-Curriculum.jpg?resize=1024%2C577&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/School-Curriculum.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/School-Curriculum.jpg?resize=768%2C433&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/School-Curriculum.jpg?resize=58%2C33&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/School-Curriculum.jpg?resize=260%2C147&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/School-Curriculum.jpg?resize=200%2C113&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/School-Curriculum.jpg?w=1448&amp;ssl=1 1448w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/School-Curriculum.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The Senate of the Yusuf Maitama Sule University, Kano (YUMSUK), has approved Monday, Jan. 18, 2021 as the resumption date for the continuation of its 2019/2020 Academic session. Abdullahi Abba-Hassan, Head of Information, Publications and Public Relations Unit of the university, disclosed this in a statement issued to newsmen on Saturday, in Kano. “The Senate made the decision at its 35th special meeting held on Jan. 14, 2021, which was chaired by the Vice-Chancellor of the University and Chairman of the University’s Senate, Prof. Mukhtar Kurawa. “The resolution is in line with the directive of the Kano State Governor, Dr. Abdullahi Umar Ganduje, on the reopening of all tertiary institutions in the state effective from Jan. 18, 2021.” “Recalls that the closure of the university was due to the outbreak of the Coronavirus pandemic, as well as the recently called off strike by the Academic Staff Union of Universities (ASUU),”, Abba Hassan said. “According to the revised academic calendar, continuation of registration for the session and that of the First Semester Lectures will begin on the resumption date.” He said the students are to strictly adhere to all safety precautions, protocols and guidelines put in place by the university with a view to containing and preventing the spread of the COVID-19. “The students and the entire University Community are enjoined to wear facemasks, observe social distancing and wash their hands at the designated points in all the campuses of the university,’’ the statement added. Vanguard News Nigeria The Senate of the Yusuf Maitama Sule University, Kano (YUMSUK), has approved Monday, Jan. 18, 2021 as the resumption date for the continuation of its 2019/2020 Academic session. Abdullahi Abba-Hassan, Head of Information, Publications and Public Relations Unit of the university, disclosed this in a statement issued to newsmen on… January 16, 2021 In "News" The Governor of Kano State His Excellency Dr Abdullahi Umar Ganduje OFR and the State Executive Council has approved the renaming of Northwest University Kano to Yusuf Maitama Sule University Kano. July 6, 2017 In "News" EXACTLY 90 days to his 88th birthday, Elder statesman and frontline nationalist, Alhaji Yusuf Maitama Sule, passed on, yesterday morning, throwing his Kano home state into mourning. July 4, 2017 In "News"